  "title": "Why Can We Regrow A Liver (But Not A Limb)?",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 874.0,
      "end_time": 3060.0,
      "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 3060.0,
      "end_time": 7490.0,
      "text": "Science Out Loud."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 7490.0,
      "end_time": 9820.0,
      "text": "Sea stars can replace severed arms."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 9820.0,
      "end_time": 12100.0,
      "text": "Flatworms can regenerate over half their bodies."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 12100.0,
      "end_time": 14800.0,
      "text": "And if a predator grabbed this lizard&#39;s tail,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 14800.0,
      "end_time": 17840.0,
      "text": "she could break it off and regrow it later."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 17840.0,
      "end_time": 19990.0,
      "text": "It would be really awesome if we could regrow limbs"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 19990.0,
      "end_time": 21230.0,
      "text": "just like lizards do."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 21230.0,
      "end_time": 22840.0,
      "text": "But we can&#39;t."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 22840.0,
      "end_time": 24830.0,
      "text": "The closest we can get is kind of, sort of"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 24830.0,
      "end_time": 25925.0,
      "text": "regenerating our livers."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 29510.0,
      "end_time": 30790.0,
      "text": "But let&#39;s back up."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 30790.0,
      "end_time": 32542.0,
      "text": "Our bodies are made of organs, which"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 32542.0,
      "end_time": 34000.0,
      "text": "are made of tissues, which are made"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 34000.0,
      "end_time": 36880.0,
      "text": "of lots of different kinds of cells, from nerve cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 36880.0,
      "end_time": 39080.0,
      "text": "to bone cells to skin cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 39080.0,
      "end_time": 41060.0,
      "text": "And our cells are constantly dying or getting"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 41060.0,
      "end_time": 42610.0,
      "text": "scraped off or bled out."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 42610.0,
      "end_time": 44770.0,
      "text": "So we need to be able to make more of them."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 44770.0,
      "end_time": 46260.0,
      "text": "So we have these things called stem"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 46260.0,
      "end_time": 48820.0,
      "text": "cells which can morph or differentiate"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 48820.0,
      "end_time": 52340.0,
      "text": "into, say, a liver cell or a blood cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 52340.0,
      "end_time": 55197.0,
      "text": "When we&#39;re embryos, our stem cells are superpowered."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 55197.0,
      "end_time": 56780.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re pluripotent, meaning that they"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 56780.0,
      "end_time": 58650.0,
      "text": "can become any sort of cell our body"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 58650.0,
      "end_time": 61440.0,
      "text": "might need and help grow everything from our stomach"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 61440.0,
      "end_time": 64480.0,
      "text": "lining to our muscles to our skin."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 64480.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67850.0,
      "text": "But as adults, our stem cells lose the superpower."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 67850.0,
      "end_time": 71949.0,
      "text": "Adult stem cells can&#39;t become just any sort of cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 71949.0,
      "end_time": 73740.0,
      "text": "While certain stem cells in our bone marrow"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 73740.0,
      "end_time": 76290.0,
      "text": "have to become either blood or immune cells,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 76290.0,
      "end_time": 79510.0,
      "text": "stem cells in our intestine have to become intestinal cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 79510.0,
      "end_time": 81230.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s no way either of these stem cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 81230.0,
      "end_time": 85176.0,
      "text": "will ever become, say, a liver cell or a nerve cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 85176.0,
      "end_time": 88480.0,
      "text": "[MUSIC PLAYING]"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 89510.0,
      "end_time": 92490.0,
      "text": "Lizards don&#39;t ever lose their stem cell superpowers."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 92490.0,
      "end_time": 95270.0,
      "text": "When a lizard&#39;s tail falls off, a bunch of pluripotent"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 95270.0,
      "end_time": 97935.0,
      "text": "stem cells rush to the stump and form this mass called"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 97935.0,
      "end_time": 100020.0,
      "text": "a regeneration blastema."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 100020.0,
      "end_time": 102390.0,
      "text": "The pluripotent stem cells will differentiate"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 102390.0,
      "end_time": 105560.0,
      "text": "into skin cells, muscle cells, or bone cells--"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 105560.0,
      "end_time": 106960.0,
      "text": "any type of cell the lizard might"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 106960.0,
      "end_time": 109190.0,
      "text": "need to regenerate a tail."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 109190.0,
      "end_time": 112160.0,
      "text": "But why can&#39;t humans regrow an arm?"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 112160.0,
      "end_time": 114600.0,
      "text": "Scientists think it&#39;s an evolutionary trade-off."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 114600.0,
      "end_time": 117180.0,
      "text": "Those lizards have small bodies and would take one of them"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 117180.0,
      "end_time": 119000.0,
      "text": "a couple weeks to regrow the tail."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 119000.0,
      "end_time": 121680.0,
      "text": "But it would take a lot more time and energy for one of us"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 121680.0,
      "end_time": 124730.0,
      "text": "to regrow a whole arm, plus the added energy it"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 124730.0,
      "end_time": 127530.0,
      "text": "takes to keep the pluripotent stem cells in reserve."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 127530.0,
      "end_time": 130440.0,
      "text": "So instead of wasting all that time and energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 130440.0,
      "end_time": 132466.0,
      "text": "we just grow some scar tissue over the wound"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 132466.0,
      "end_time": 133840.0,
      "text": "and learn to live without an arm."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 136650.0,
      "end_time": 138960.0,
      "text": "But our livers are a little bit different."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 138960.0,
      "end_time": 141000.0,
      "text": "The liver is our biggest internal organ."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 141000.0,
      "end_time": 143340.0,
      "text": "And it helps with digestion, stores nutrients"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 143340.0,
      "end_time": 146522.0,
      "text": "and immune signals, and filters waste from our blood."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 146522.0,
      "end_time": 147980.0,
      "text": "If your liver shut down completely,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 147980.0,
      "end_time": 149375.0,
      "text": "we would die in a couple days."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 149375.0,
      "end_time": 152280.0,
      "text": "So we&#39;ve evolved to protect against that."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 152280.0,
      "end_time": 157520.0,
      "text": "Turns out that even if you lost 75% of your liver,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 157520.0,
      "end_time": 160160.0,
      "text": "the remaining liver cells could grow and divide"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 160160.0,
      "end_time": 162740.0,
      "text": "and reform a mass of liver tissue."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 162740.0,
      "end_time": 165910.0,
      "text": "The sort of regrown liver isn&#39;t coming from stem cells, though."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 165910.0,
      "end_time": 169310.0,
      "text": "So the structure won&#39;t be quite the same as the original."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 169310.0,
      "end_time": 172560.0,
      "text": "So this isn&#39;t true regeneration like with a lizard&#39;s tail."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 172560.0,
      "end_time": 175660.0,
      "text": "But the liver will function well enough to keep you alive."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 175660.0,
      "end_time": 177740.0,
      "text": "But what if your liver fails so badly"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 177740.0,
      "end_time": 179676.0,
      "text": "that your body can&#39;t fix it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 179676.0,
      "end_time": 181050.0,
      "text": "Couldn&#39;t you just cut off a piece"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 181050.0,
      "end_time": 183130.0,
      "text": "of, say, your sister&#39;s healthy liver,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 183130.0,
      "end_time": 185220.0,
      "text": "grow a new one in this tissue culture lab,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 185220.0,
      "end_time": 187100.0,
      "text": "and then transplant it into you?"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 187100.0,
      "end_time": 189760.0,
      "text": "The problem is that liver cells don&#39;t survive long enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 189760.0,
      "end_time": 193330.0,
      "text": "outside the body to grow into enough tissue to transplant."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 193330.0,
      "end_time": 196400.0,
      "text": "Scientists at MIT&#39;s Lab for Multiscale Regenerative"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 196400.0,
      "end_time": 199200.0,
      "text": "Technologies are trying to solve this problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 199200.0,
      "end_time": 201160.0,
      "text": "How can we mimic the human body&#39;s environment"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 201160.0,
      "end_time": 203040.0,
      "text": "in the lab to allow liver cells to grow"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 203040.0,
      "end_time": 205360.0,
      "text": "into fully functional livers?"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 205360.0,
      "end_time": 207830.0,
      "text": "And livers are just the beginning."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 207830.0,
      "end_time": 210290.0,
      "text": "For example, other organ cells, like the ones"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 210290.0,
      "end_time": 213390.0,
      "text": "in your heart and brain, don&#39;t divide like liver cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 213390.0,
      "end_time": 215920.0,
      "text": "Researchers are finding ways to trick them and stem"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 215920.0,
      "end_time": 218610.0,
      "text": "cells to someday regenerate those organs and other body"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 218610.0,
      "end_time": 220150.0,
      "text": "parts, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 220150.0,
      "end_time": 222960.0,
      "text": "So for now, our reptile friends have one-upped us."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 222960.0,
      "end_time": 224470.0,
      "text": "But we&#39;re catching up."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 224470.0,
      "end_time": 225565.0,
      "text": "Watch out, little buddies."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 229850.0,
      "end_time": 230350.0,
      "text": "Hi."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 230350.0,
      "end_time": 231100.0,
      "text": "This is Sari."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
